title: Watch: First look at Helen Flanagan back on Coronation Street as Rosie Webster
text:

Rosie Webster throws her arms around her shocked dad Kevin when she returns to Coronation Street on Monday night. 
Model Rosie, played by Helen Flanagan , looks as glamorous as ever as she makes a comeback to Weatherfield from Miami with her little sister Sophie, played by Brooke Vincent. 
At first Kevin thinks that Sophie has flown back home alone as she steps out of the taxi, and his girlfriend Anna Windass remarks “what have you got there? half of duty free?” 
But then he can’t believe it when eldest daughter Rosie jumps out too and throws her arms around him. 
Still wearing her pink sleep mask from the flight over her brunette tresses she shrieks “it’s me dad can you believe it?” as a delighted Kev twirls her around on the cobbles. 
She then turns to a stunned Anna, says “hi” and flashes a big smile at the cafe worker, who stares in amazement. Rosie is reunited with her dad Kevin (Photo: ITV) 
As well as a load of luggage, it seems that the girls have brought a whole lot of trouble back to Coronation Street with them, when the police search Rosie and Sophie Webster’s belongings. 
But what has Rosie been caught up in? And does this spell more misery for mechanic Kevin who admits he’s in financial difficulty because of her medical bill, the loss of his tow truck and the recent fire at the garage? 
Bury actress Helen has said her formerly self-centred character comes back a nicer person after spending five years away from Weatherfield. And she is delighted to be back on the ITV1 soap. Sophie Webster arrives home from Miami with big sister Rosie (Photo: ITV) Read More Helen Flanagan says we'll be seeing a different Rosie Webster on Coronation Street 
Helen, who welcomed her little girl Matilda in 2015, said: “It’s completely different because I left when I was 21 and I’m 26 now. 
“Obviously I’ve matured now and obviously now I’ve got a little girl, which makes you grow up a lot. So I see it completely different now I’ve come back.” Read More
